<p><i><b>Master of Magic</b></i> is a single-player, <a href="/wiki/Fantasy" title="Fantasy">fantasy</a> <a href="/wiki/Turn-based_strategy" title="Turn-based strategy">turn-based strategy</a> computer game created by <a href="/wiki/Simtex" title="Simtex">Simtex</a> and published by <a href="/wiki/Microprose" title="Microprose" class="mw-redirect">Microprose</a> in <a href="/wiki/1994_in_video_gaming" title="1994 in video gaming">1994</a><sup id="cite_ref-Moby_0-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Moby-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>. The player controls a <a href="/wiki/Wizard_(fantasy)" title="Wizard (fantasy)" class="mw-redirect">wizard</a> attempting to rule two worlds. From a small settlement, the player must grow an empire and banish all the other wizards by military might or casting the Spell of Mastery. To do this, the player must manage resources, build cities and armies, and research spells. <i>Master of Magic</i>'s early versions had many bugs, and was heavily criticized by reviewers.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
